Following two weeks of tension caused by Iraqi accusations of Kuwaiti harmful  wrongdoing; Iraq invaded and quickly overran Kuwaiti defenses.
Kuwait's leaders  escaped to Saudi Arabia, however, the emir's brother was killed defending the palace.
Iraq's government said it invaded at the request of revolutionaries who had already  staged a coup.
It was the first time in modern history that one Arab nation invaded  another.
The al Sabah family has ruled the city-state of Kuwait for almost 250 years.
The "provisional government" announced that it was dissolving Kuwait's parliament and  would soon hold "free and honest elections."
